Program: Great Lives
Title: W H Auden
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gj8nv
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 29 Aug 2006
Presenter Matthew Parris and journalist Jeremy Vine dispute the relative merits and attractions of W H Auden's poetry, while biographer Richard Davenport-Hines believes that you need to understand the man's life to appreciate his work.